This paper deals with data-intensive applications on clusters, which involves distributed computing and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses sorted tree structures, which are commonly used in data structures and algorithms, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely category. The use of networks for query processing and packet routing suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as a possible category. The paper also mentions query processing in database systems, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper proposes a solution for improving performance, which could be considered as a system-level optimization, indicating cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category.
